ContiTech Invests in Serbian Plant, Production to Start in 2012

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-09-22T12:18:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/contitech-invests-in-serbian-plant-production-to-start-in-2012.html
ContiTech AG, a unit of  Continental
AG (CON) , will start producing hose lines for the automotive industry
at its new plant in  Serbia  next year, investing over 10 million
euros ($13.46 million) there.  The plant will have a workforce of 300 by 2016, the company
said in an e-mailed statement today. Construction will start by
November, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  